'''Yehvann Djibril Victor Diouf''' (born 16 November 1999) is a professional [[association football|football]]er who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]] for {{French football updater|Nice}} club [[OGC Nice|Nice]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
On 8 September 2016, Diouf became the youngest ever player to sign a professional contract with [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]], at the age of 16 years and 297 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.estac.fr/actualites/15798/premier-contrat-pro-pour-yehvann-diouf.html|title=Premier contrat pro pour Yehvann Diouf - ESTAC.FR|website=www.estac.fr|access-date=20 May 2019|archive-date=5 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221105004741/https://www.estac.fr/actualites/15798/premier-contrat-pro-pour-yehvann-diouf.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his professional debut for Troyes in a 0–0 [[Ligue 2]] tie with [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] on 17 May 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/85369|title=ESTAC Troyes - AC Ajaccio (0-0) - Saison 2018/2019 - Domino's Ligue 2|website=www.lfp.fr}}</ref>

Diouf signed a four-year contract to join [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] starting 1 July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-yehvann-diouf-troyes-rejoindra-reims-l-ete-prochain/973715|title=Transferts : Yehvann Diouf (Troyes) rejoindra Reims l'été prochain|website=L'ÉQUIPE}}</ref>

On 3 July 2025, it was announced that Diouf would sign for fellow [[Ligue 1]] club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] for a fee of €7 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-03 |title=Official {{!}} Yehvann Diouf joins OGC Nice from Reims in €7m deal - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2025/official-yehvann-diouf-joins-ogc-nice-from-reims-in-e7m-deal/ |access-date=2025-07-03 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Diouf is of Senegalese and Polish descent through his father and mother, respectively.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tomegah |first1=Rodolph |title=Yehvann Diouf: Ce jeune gardien d'origine sénégalaise que veut Chelsea |url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2016/04/12/yehvann-diouf-ce-jeune-gardien-dorigine-senegalaise-que-veut-chelsea/ |website=Africa Top Sports |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160412222245/https://www.africatopsports.com/2016/04/12/yehvann-diouf-ce-jeune-gardien-dorigine-senegalaise-que-veut-chelsea/ |archive-date=12 April 2016 |language=fr-FR |date=12 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://emedia.sn/yehvann-diouf-un-renfort-de-poids-pour-les-lions/|title=Yehvann Diouf, un renfort de poids pour les Lions|date=13 March 2025 }}</ref> He represented the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]]s at the [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/182040-la-liste-des-u19-pour-l-euro-2018?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/ |title=La Liste Des U19 Pour L'EURO 2018 |trans-title= U19 List for the EURO 2018 |website=fff.fr |access-date=15 July 2018 |language=fr |date=12 July 2018}}</ref>

On 19 March 2025, Diouf's request to switch international allegiance to [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change"/>

